reviewText: An excellent script, graced by first rate performers. This movie is much more than a comedy: it's almost a mirror. It makes you reflect on the pathetic black comedy family life -and human condition- usually is. I only wish it was already available on DVD...

reviewText: William Peterson's showcase performance as a sympathetic prototype of Dan Quayle proves that, long before CSI, he was capable of complex subtlety and timing.  This ensemble piece does well with the "eccentric family" genre, and can be thanked in passing for featuring a human but non-degenerate priest--a rarity in movies for decades now.

reviewText: Good fun movie. Very goofy craziness, it leaves you shaking your head and laughing. You might even find yourself a wee bit embarrassed for the lead male character, but he sails on thru til you end up almost needing to go to the bathroom due to  laughter. A solid thumbs UP.

reviewText: I rented this movie because it featured several of my favorite actors (Hoskins, Peterson, McDormand, Curry), and I was hopeful of the "crazy family" plot. What can I say? It has interesting and genuinely hilarious moments, but several completely asinine complications. The ending is so derivative and predictable, it's embarrassing. Mostly definitely a "B" if not "C+" movie; but Hoskins is as watchable as ever, so thank God his role dominates.

reviewText: I first saw this film when it was new - I thought it was great, it still IS!It's witty and funny and sad all in one.Somehow I don't think it ever got the recognition it deserved, it should have.Here's a great cast, acting, writing - all of it comes together in a film that is well worth watching.Please don't miss it, with what little Hollywoood has to offer lately, this film is a real Gem!
